<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>in flight • on the fly</xh5><p> <i>in flight—</i>1. while flying: Gliders are now fitted with a means of cleaning off the leading edges of the wings <u>in flight</u>. 2. running away; fleeing: The two men are hiding in a hotel apparently <u>in flight</u> from the police.</p><p><i>on the fly</i>—1. <i>= in flight 1: </i>Peregrine falcons are predators and their prey consists mainly of birds, caught <u>on the fly</u>. 2. in motion; moving fast: She is constantly <u>on the fly</u> as she directs, plays piano or walks through the rows of children. 3. <i>do smth. </i>quickly or in passing (while busy with other things): Changes must be made <u>on the fly</u>, as the program progresses. 4. <i>(sl.)</i> having a lively, merry time; on the spree: My father had been <u>on the fly</u> in that town for nine or ten days.</p> </entry>
